  "title": "Aesthetic Residence  Doctor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>This role is responsible for delivering scientifically proven, evidence-based medical aesthetic and age management treatments in a clinical setting, driving patient satisfaction and treatment efficacy through expert consultation and procedure administration.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform medical-grade aesthetic treatments including injectables (Botox, skin boosters, fillers), Pico Laser, Helio laser treatments, chemical peels, and thread lifts to achieve optimal patient outcomes</li><li>Develop and implement personalized patient treatment plans by assessing patient concerns and recommending appropriate evidence-based therapies</li><li>Conduct thorough patient consultations to educate and advise on treatment options and expected results</li><li>Monitor and review patient progress against treatment plans to ensure effectiveness and adjust protocols as needed</li><li>Maintain high standards of clinical care and patient safety throughout all procedures</li><li>Manage patient enquiries by providing clear, accurate information about treatment courses and care instructions</li><li>Train and mentor clinical staff to uphold quality and compliance standards within the medical aesthetic practice</li><li>Foster a collaborative, respectful workplace culture that supports performance excellence and patient-centered care</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Medical degree: MBBS, MBChB, MBBCh, MD or equivalent</li><li>Registration with the Singapore Medical Council</li><li>Attainment of all relevant Certificate of Competence (COCs) for medical aesthetic procedures</li></ul>",
